We must consider the table given. 

Now, determine the period to calculate the annual percentage rate is the EAR is 11.1% and compounded semi-annually.

Since the rate, we're trying to solve an annual rate, and the compounding period is semi-annual, we will divide the twelve months of the year by semi-annual, which is six months, to determine the period to be used.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Compounding period} &= \dfrac{12\text{ months}}{6\text{ months}}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{2}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the compounding period we will consider in our calculation is 2.

Next, calculate the compounding period to be used if the EAR is 19.6% and compounded monthly.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Compounding period} &= \dfrac{12\text{ months}}{1\text{ month}}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{12}
\end{aligned}$$

The compounding period is monthly; hence in determining the annual percentage rate, we will use a compounding period of 12, representing the number of months in a year.
